More than 200 attacks on EMS staff have been recorded in the Western Cape between 2012 and 2016. CAPE TOWN - The Western Cape Health Department says attacks on paramedics are taking place in communities that are most in need of medical services.More than 200 attacks on EMS staff have been recorded in the Western Cape between 2012 and 2016. Problem areas include Hanover Park, Fafelisig and Site C in Khayelitsha.The department s Beth Engelbrecht said: Clearly we are dealing with a societal issue of violence and attack. And if anything in our ambulances seems to be of value, that becomes a key driver of these attacks. So we are extremely concerned. Last week an ambulance crew was held up at gunpoint in Khayelitsha.